                <h1>Causes of Red Flags in Background Checks</h1>
                <p>A red flag on a background check can arise from various issues, including criminal records, inconsistent employment history, poor credit reports, or discrepancies in provided information. These flags may signal potential risks to employers, causing concern about an applicant’s reliability or trustworthiness. Understanding these factors is crucial for job seekers.</p>
